{"questionId":"6020","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When a spaceship passes the Earth, an observer on the Earth and an observer on the&nbsp;spaceship both start clocks. The initial time on both clocks is 12 midnight. The spaceship&nbsp;is travelling at a constant velocity with <em>γ</em> = 1.25. A space station is stationary relative to the&nbsp;Earth and carries clocks that also read Earth time.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Some of the radio signal is reflected at the surface of the Earth and this reflected&nbsp;signal is later detected at the spaceship. The detection of this signal is event B.&nbsp;The spacetime diagram is shown for the Earth, showing the space station and&nbsp;the spaceship. Both axes are drawn to the same scale.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b00352ad4e3a4a89229b3a9de9c14a06d2e0546d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate, using the spacetime diagram, the time at which event B occurs for&nbsp;the spaceship.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>In spaceship frame<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>Finds the ratio <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{OB}}{{OE}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>O</mi>\n      <mi>B</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>O</mi>\n      <mi>E</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> (or by similar triangles on <em>x </em>or&nbsp;<em>ct </em>axes), value is approximately 4</p>\n<p>hence time elapsed ≈&nbsp;4 ×&nbsp;90 mins ≈&nbsp;6h&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>so clock time is ≈&nbsp;6:00<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>Alternative 1:</em></strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4764/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_06.33.50.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/04.d.ii/M\"></p>\n<p><em>Allow similar triangles using </em><em>x</em><em>-axis or ct-axis, such as </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{distance\\,2}}{{distance\\,1}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>&nbsp;from diagrams below</em></p>\n<p><em><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4766/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_06.52.27.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/04.d.ii_02/M\"></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>In Earth frame<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>Finds the ratio</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ct{\\text{ coordinate of B}}}}{{ct{\\text{ coordinate of A}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;coordinate of B</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;coordinate of A</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>, value is approximately 2.5</p>\n<p>hence time elapsed&nbsp;≈&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2.5 \\times 3{\\text{h}}}}{{1.25}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.5</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>h</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.25</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≈&nbsp;6h</p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>so clocktime is ≈ 6:00<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2:</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4767/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_06.53.38.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/04.d.ii_03/M\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6020","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.4d.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Estimate, using the spacetime diagram, the time at which event B occurs for the spaceship.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.3 – Spacetime diagrams","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}